# NeRF 3D Scene Reconstruction

Neural Radiance Fields (NeRF) implementation for 3D scene reconstruction from 2D images.

## How to Run

```bash
# 1. Install dependencies
pip install -r requirements.txt

# 2. (Optional) Add your own images to data/nerf_images/
#    Otherwise synthetic images are used automatically.

# 3. Run
python nerf_reconstruction.py
```

## Outputs
| File | Description |
|------|-------------|
| `sample_views.png` | Input viewpoint images |
| `training_loss.png` | Loss curve over training epochs |
| `point_cloud_3d.png` | 3D point cloud coloured by density |
| `evaluation_metrics.png` | PSNR & SSIM bar charts |